[Milestone 2] Strict gate not met (no config satisfies all three conditions).

  Key finding (Phase 1b — the safety-aware sweet spot):
  - Proposed α=0.5 (balanced): M4=0.0016 (vs B2 0.4671), M7obs=1.00, M1=0.00.
    It RESTRICTS (read_only) rather than denies, so it stops nearly all
    FDI while keeping the EMS fully sighted — the trade-off B2/B4 cannot make.

  Trade-off gradient (security ↔ safety, via α):
    α=0.8 (security-dominant): over-denies → M7obs≈0 (EMS blinded, like B2/B4)
    α=0.5 (balanced):          M4≈0 AND M7obs=1.0 — the headline result
    α=0.2 (safety-dominant):   keeps nodes full → pa at ceiling, zero denial cost
    B2 (FENG greedy):          comparable security, M7=inf (EMS blinded)

  Narrative: a trade-off (balance preserves visibility while collapsing pa) —
  NOT 'beats FENG on security'. The independent M7 axis is what distinguishes them.
